<docs>
	<doc for="ScrollEventHandler">
		<summary>
			<para>Represents the method that handles the
      <see langword="Scroll"/> event of a <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ScrollBar"/>, <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.TrackBar"/>, or
      <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.DataGrid"/>.</para>
		</summary>
		<param name="sender">The source of the event.</param>
		<param name="e">A <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ScrollEventArgs"/> that contains the event data.</param>
		<remarks>
			<para>When you create a <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ScrollEventArgs"/> delegate, you
   identify the method that will handle the event. To associate the event with your
   event handler, add an instance of the delegate to the event. The event handler
   is called whenever the event occurs, unless you remove the delegate. For more
   information about event handler delegates, see <see topic="cpconEventsDelegates"/>.</para>
		</remarks>
		<example>
			<codelink SampleID="Classic ScrollBar.OnScroll Example" SnippetID="1"/>
		</example>
		<seealso cref="System.Windows.Forms.ScrollBar"/>
		<seealso cref="System.Windows.Forms.TrackBar"/>
		<seealso cref="System.Windows.Forms.DataGrid"/>
	</doc>
</docs>
